text: Significant main effects of time by group interaction for fractional anisotropy and radial diffusivity of the left and right superior cerebellar peduncles were found ( F2 ,23 range , 5.555-3 .450 ; P = .036 -.088 after false discovery rate correction ) .

Significantly different improvements in insulin resistance ( P < 0.0001 ) , blood pressure ( P < 0.0001 ) , and lipid peroxidation ( P = 0.001 ) were also observed for the HF and IF groups in comparison with the LF group .

The psychometric analysis supports the application of the self-regulation model to ageing perceptions , but also the existence of distinct `` physical decline '' and `` ongoing development '' dimensions of perceptions .
